text: Phillicia Sprauve (born 3 August 1960) is a retired United States Virgin Islands taekwondo athlete. She competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the heavyweight event. At the 1986 Pan American Taekwondo Championships she won the bronze medal in the +70 kg category. == References == == Other websites == * Tae Kwon Do Champions - U.S. Virgin Islands - Phillicia Sprauve - Taekwondo Hall Of Fame Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:Taekwondo practitioners Category:American martial artists Category:United States Virgin Islands
